This paper discusses the social and technical environment in which Wikipedia's bots operate, and the establishment and role of English Wikipedia's bot policies and the Bot Approvals Group. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer and Society (cs.CY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of bots in monitoring and moderating content, which could fall under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper also examines the negotiation of rules around bot operation, which could fall under the Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the role of bots in enforcing social norms, which could fall under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms in user-generated content platforms, which could fall under the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category.
